Interface IEnumUtils

All Known Implementing Classes:
EnumUtils
public interface IEnumUtils

For those projects that require full, static-free mocking capabilities, use this interface. Else, the concrete implementation EnumUtils or EnumUtils.INSTANCE will suffice.

Author:
Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
See Also:

Method Detail

valueOf

<TEnum extends Enum<TEnum>> TEnum valueOf(Class<TEnum> enumType,
                                          String name)
Drop-in replacement for Enum.valueOf(Class, String) with better exception message.

To suppress exception on failed lookup, see tryValueOf(Class, String).

Type Parameters:
TEnum - type name for enum, e.g., Fruit
Parameters:
enumType - class object for enum type, e.g., Fruit.class
name - name of enum constant, e.g., Fruit.BANANA -> "BANANA"
Returns:
enum value for name
Throws:
NullPointerException - if enumType or name is null
IllegalArgumentException -
  • if name is empty or only whitespace
  • if name is not a member of enum type
See Also:
Enum.valueOf(Class, String), tryValueOf(Class, String)

tryValueOf

<TEnum extends Enum<TEnum>> TEnum tryValueOf(Class<TEnum> enumType,
                                             String name)
Convenience method for valueOf(Class, String), but IllegalArgumentException is suppressed on failed lookup, and null is instead returned.
